AN ACT relating to agriculture; requiring the Director of the State
Department of Agriculture to establish a program to assist
in the development of community gardens and urban
farms in areas of this State with high levels of food
insecurity; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Director of the State Department of Agriculture to
2 establish certain programs relating to the supply of food in this State, including the
3 Supplemental Food Program and the Home Feeds Nevada Agriculture Food
4 Purchase Program. (NRS 561.495, 561.515) Existing law further sets forth various
5 provisions to encourage the development of community gardens and urban farms in
6 this State which: (1) require certain entities to promote or encourage such
7 development; (2) authorize certain entities to use or lease certain land for the
8 purpose of community gardening or urban farming; and (3) authorize a partial
9 abatement of certain taxes for a parcel on which a community garden or urban farm
10 is located. (NRS 232.4968, 244.291, 244.339, 268.0191, 408.507, 528.135)
11 This bill requires the Director to establish a program to assist in the
12 development of community gardens and urban farms in areas of this State with high
13 levels of food insecurity, including, without limitation, areas that have been
14 designated as food deserts. This bill further authorizes the Director to apply for and
15 accept any gift, donation, bequest, grant or other source of money for the purpose
16 of funding such a program.
